'''Hjalmar Ekdal''' ({{IPA|sv|ˈjǎlmar ˈêːkdɑːl|Lang}}; born 21 October 1998) is a Swedish professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for {{English football updater|Burnley}} club [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] and the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]]. He is the younger brother of former footballer [[Albin Ekdal]].

Beginning his professional career with [[IK Frej]] in 2018, Ekdal briefly represented [[Assyriska FF]], [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]], and [[IK Sirius Fotboll|IK Sirius]] before signing with [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] in 2021.

==Club career==
===Early career===
Ekdal was born in Stockholm and started to play football with [[IF Brommapojkarna]] as a youngster.<ref name="bpbror">{{cite web|url=https://www.expressen.se/gt/sport/hjalmar-ekdal-vill-ga-i-brorsans-fotspar/|title=Hjalmar Ekdal vill gå i brorsans fotspår|accessdate=10 February 2020|date=15 July 2014|publisher=Expressen|language=Swedish}}</ref> In 2017, he left to club to study in the [[United States]] and play college soccer for [[UNC Wilmington Seahawks]].<ref name="lämnabp">{{cite web|url=http://ifbp.se/forening/stensson-och-ekdal-till-usa-fors-tranar-med-herrlaget/|title=Stensson och Ekdal till USA – Fors tränar med herrlaget|date=28 June 2017 |accessdate=10 February 2020|publisher=IF Brommapojkarna|language=Swedish}}</ref> While in the US, he played in 20 games and scored two goals as the Seahawks reached the final of the [[2017 CAA Men's Soccer Tournament]] before losing 4–2 to [[William & Mary Tribe men's soccer|William & Mary Tribe]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Men's Soccer vs William & Mary (CAA Championship) on 11/12/2017 - Box Score|url=https://uncwsports.com/sports/mens-soccer/stats/2017/william-mary-caa-championship-/boxscore/6346|access-date=14 October 2021|website=UNC Wilmington Athletics|language=en}}</ref>

===IK Frej===
In May 2018, Ekdal returned to his native country and signed a two-year deal with [[IK Frej]] in [[Superettan]], Sweden's second tier.<ref name="klarfrej">{{cite web|url=https://fotbolltransfers.com/site/news/91891|title=Officiellt: IK Frej Täby värvar Hjalmar Ekdal|access-date=10 February 2020|date=9 April 2018|publisher=Fotbolltransfers.com|language=Swedish}}</ref> He played 15 league games throughout the year, scoring once, as the club finished 9th in the table.<ref name="svff">{{cite web|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/superettan/information/?scr=player&fplid=6078f6de-cc92-46f5-a3a6-450727bf5912|title=Spelarstatistik: Hjalmar Ekdal|accessdate=10 February 2010|publisher=Swedish Football Association|language=Swedish}}</ref> Ekdal also made one appearance out on loan with [[Assyriska FF]] in [[Division 1 (Swedish football)|Division 1]], the third tier.<ref name="assyriska">{{cite web|url=http://assyriska.se/index.php?id=27&articleID=3455&page=6&filter_year=0&filter_text=|title=Samarbetsavtal med IK Frej|accessdate=10 February 2020|date=9 June 2018|publisher=Assyriska FF|language=Swedish}}{{Dead link|date=August 2024 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>

In 2019, Ekdal had a major breakthrough and established himself in the starting eleven at IK Frej.<ref name="frejbajen">{{cite web|url=https://www.laget.se/ikfrejherr/News/6028929/Hjalmar-Ekdal-lamnar-IK-Frej-Taby-for-Hammarby-IF|title=Hjalmar Ekdal lämnar IK Frej Täby för Hammarby IF|accessdate=10 February 2020|date=19 July 2018|publisher=IK Frej|language=Swedish|archive-date=27 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220727183036/https://www.laget.se/ikfrejherr/News/6028929/Hjalmar-Ekdal-lamnar-IK-Frej-Taby-for-Hammarby-IF|url-status=dead}}</ref> He played all 30 league games in Superettan during the season, scoring twice, but was unable to save the club from relegation.<ref name="svff"/>

===Hammarby IF===
On 19 July 2019, Ekdal transferred to [[Hammarby Fotboll|Hammarby IF]] in [[Allsvenskan]], signing a two-year deal.<ref name="hammarbysigned">{{cite web|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hjalmar-ekdal-klar-for-hammarby/|title=Hjalmar Ekdal klar för Hammarby|accessdate=10 February 2020|date=19 July 2019|publisher=Hammarby IF|language=Swedish|archive-date=23 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423065554/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hjalmar-ekdal-klar-for-hammarby/|url-status=dead}}</ref> It was also announced that he would remain eligible for affiliated club IK Frej for the rest of the season.<ref name="frejbajen"/> On 3 March 2020, Ekdal was sent on loan to fellow Allsvenskan club [[IK Sirius Fotboll|IK Sirius]] for the remainder of the season.<ref name="siriusloan">{{cite web|url=https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hjalmar-ekdal-lanas-ut-till-ik-sirius/|title=Hjalmar Ekdal lånas ut till IK Sirius|accessdate=3 March 2020|date=3 March 2020|publisher=Hammarby IF|language=Swedish|archive-date=23 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230423051036/https://www.hammarbyfotboll.se/aktuellt/nyheter/hjalmar-ekdal-lanas-ut-till-ik-sirius/|url-status=dead}}</ref>

=== Djurgårdens IF ===
On 4 January 2021, Ekdal joined [[Djurgårdens IF Fotboll|Djurgårdens IF]] on a four-year contract.<ref>{{Cite web|date=4 January 2021|title=Hjalmar Ekdal klar för DIF|url=https://dif.se/nyheter/nyhetsarkiv/2021/hjalmar-ekdal-klar-for-dif|access-date=18 October 2021|website=Djurgården Fotboll}}</ref> He was named the Allsvenskan player of the month for the month of September 2021.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|date=12 October 2021|title=Hjalmar Ekdal och Henrik Rydström är september månads vinnare i Allsvenskan|url=https://www.svenskelitfotboll.se/hjalmar-ekdal-och-henrik-rydstrom-ar-september-manads-vinnare-i-allsvenskan/|access-date=18 October 2021|website=Föreningen Svensk Elitfotboll|language=sv-SE}}</ref>

===Burnley===
On 21 January 2023, Ekdal moved to England and joined [[EFL Championship|Championship]] leaders [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] on a four-and-a-half-year deal for an undisclosed fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/content/ekdal-arrives-at-turf-moor|title=EKDAL ARRIVES AT TURF MOOR|website=www.burnleyfootballclub.com|date=21 January 2023|accessdate=21 January 2023}}</ref> He earned his debut appearance for the ''Clarets'' on 4 February in a 3–0 away win against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]] in the [[2022–23 EFL Championship|EFL Championship]], in which he scored his first Burnley goal in the 60th minute.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.burnleyfootballclub.com/content/ekdal-enjoys-dream-debut |title=Ekdal enjoys dream debut |publisher=Burnley F.C. |date=4 February 2023 }}</ref>

On 23 January 2025, Ekdal joined [[Eredivisie]] club [[FC Groningen|Groningen]] on loan until the end of the season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-01-23 |title=Burnley: Sweden defender Hjalmar Ekdal joins Groningen on loan |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cgkjdvnm12do |access-date=2025-01-23 |website=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

==International career==

=== Youth ===

Ekdal was called up to the [[Sweden men's national under-19 football team|Sweden under-19 national team]] in October 2018,<ref name="frejnational">{{cite web|url=https://www.laget.se/ikfrejherr/News/5715832/Dusan-Jajic-och-Hjalmar-Ekdal-uttagna-till-U20-landslaget|title=Dusan Jajic och Hjalmar Ekdal uttagna till U20-landslaget|accessdate=10 February 2020|date=10 October 2018|publisher=IK Frej|language=Swedish|archive-date=27 July 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220727183034/https://www.laget.se/ikfrejherr/News/5715832/Dusan-Jajic-och-Hjalmar-Ekdal-uttagna-till-U20-landslaget|url-status=dead}}</ref> and featured in two friendlies against [[Denmark national under-19 football team|Denmark]] (3–1 win) and [[Russia national under-19 football team|Russia]] (1–1 draw) the same month.<ref name="ntprofile">{{cite web|url=https://www2.svenskfotboll.se/landslag/landslagsdatabas/landslagsspelare/?fplid=6078f6de-cc92-46f5-a3a6-450727bf5912|title=Landslagsdatabasen: Hjalmar Ekdal|accessdate=10 February 2020|publisher=Swedish Football Association|language=Swedish}}</ref> He was called up to the [[Sweden national under-21 football team|Sweden U21]] team for the first time on 26 August 2020.<ref>{{Cite web|title=U21-truppen till EM-kvalet - Svensk fotboll|url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/nyheter/landslag/2020/8/u21-truppen-till-em-kvalet/|access-date=26 August 2020|website=www.svenskfotboll.se|date=26 August 2020 |language=sv}}</ref>

=== Senior ===
Ekdal was called up to the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] for the first time on 1 December 2021, for two friendlies against [[Finland national football team|Finland]] in January 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Klart: Här är Sveriges trupp till januariturnén |url=https://www.fotbollskanalen.se/sverige/klart-har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-januariturnen/ |access-date=23 May 2022 |website=fotbollskanalen |language=sv}}</ref> However, the friendlies were cancelled two weeks later because of the [[COVID-19 pandemic]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=Januariturnén ställs in efter ökad smittspridning |url=https://www.aftonbladet.se/a/G3nM9Q |access-date=23 May 2022 |website=www.aftonbladet.se |date=16 December 2021 |language=sv}}</ref> Ekdal was once again called up to the national team on 18 May 2022, for Sweden's [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]] games against [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]], [[Norway national football team|Norway]], and [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]] in June 2022.<ref>{{Cite web |date=18 May 2022 |title=Hjalmar Ekdal uttagen i A-landslaget |url=https://dif.se/nyheter/nyhetsarkiv/2022/hjalmar-ekdal-uttagen-i-a-landslaget |access-date=23 May 2022 |website=Djurgården Fotboll}}</ref>

He made his full international debut for Sweden on 9 June 2022 in the UEFA Nations League game against [[Serbia national football team|Serbia]], playing the full 90 minutes at centre back in a 1–0 loss.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sverige - Serbien - Matchfakta - Svensk fotboll |url=https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-serbien-landskamper-herr-senior/5055663/ |access-date=10 June 2022 |website=www.svenskfotboll.se |language=sv |archive-date=19 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230719222851/https://www.svenskfotboll.se/matchfakta/sverige-serbien-landskamper-herr-senior/5055663/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

On 12 May 2026, Ekdal was named in the Sweden squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-05-12 |title=Mystiskt inlägg efter petningen |url=https://www.expressen.se/sport/fotboll/landslaget/har-ar-sveriges-trupp-till-fotbolls-vm-2026/ |access-date=2026-05-15 |website=www.expressen.se |language=sv}}</ref>

==Personal life==
He is the son of television host [[Lennart Ekdal]] and the younger brother of retired footballer [[Albin Ekdal]], who previously played in the [[Allsvenskan]], [[Serie A]] and [[Bundesliga]], as well as representing the [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden national team]] at senior level from 2011 to 2023.<ref name="us profile"/><ref name="bpbror"/>

